<recipe>
    <name>Smashed Potatoes with Prosciutto and Cheese</name>
    <indexCharacter>S</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>Place potatoes in a pot, cover them with water, then bring water up to a boil; salt it and cook potatoes until fork-tender, 10 to 12 minutes or so. 

Drain potatoes and add them back to warm pot. Add half of the milk sauce to potatoes with prosciutto and 1/2 cup of parmesan cheese, a couple of handfuls. Smash the potatoes to desired consistency and season with salt and pepper to taste.</instructions>
    <ingredients>
